Which product sales have been high or which products had low sales?\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa400\partightenfactor0
\cf4 \cb3 The answer is simple- They use an automated system that helps them in managing their stocks. Stock Management system helps a retailer or shopkeeper in minimizing their stocks in accordance with the sales. How this system Works\'a0So now let me tell you how the system works. We will understand this with an example of a retailer selling items to its customer as an example.\cb1 \
\cb3 Suppose you are shopping in a mart. Now when you have picked up the items you intend to buy, you will go to the billing point.\'a0Here the salesperson will scan the bar code of each of the items you have picked up. Now the software will interpret the bar code of each of the items and match it with those available in the database of the system.\cb1 \
\cb3 By this procedure, the Manager can track the sales of the items from its shop. The system now gives a clear picture to the manager about the total sales and items available in the stock. It tells him/her the quantities present on shelves or in the warehouse. So now the manager can decide which items have sufficient stock or which items needs reordering.\cb1 \
\cb3 The reordering of items is also provided by the Stock Management System. It has an interface to communicate with vendors providing the required goods. The order is placed and payment is done with the use of the Internet.\'a0Now let me tell you what happens when the reordered items reach the warehouse.\cb1 \
\cb3 The item is added into the warehouse by reading its bar code through a bar-code scanner and its quantity is updated into the system.\'a0If any new item is ordered then the details of the new product are added to the system. Its barcode and quantity are added to the system. This bar code stored in the system is matched at the time of billing to update the items in stock.\'a0Now let me tell you about the features of this software.\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa400\partightenfactor0

